00:34.910 --> 00:37.386
BRONACH: Come away, oh, human child,

00:42.000 --> 00:44.143
to the waters and the wild

00:47.381 --> 00:50.650
with a fairy, hand in hand,

00:55.180 --> 00:57.207
for the world's more full of weeping

00:57.307 --> 00:59.367
than you can understand.

01:04.480 --> 01:06.582
(BRONACH SINGING IN IRISH GAELIC)

01:21.498 --> 01:22.598
(BARKS)

01:23.000 --> 01:25.569
Will you try it with me, Ben?

01:25.669 --> 01:26.904
Okay.

01:27.004 --> 01:28.437
(SINGING IN IRISH GAELIC)

01:31.175 --> 01:33.150
Uh... I forget.

01:33.343 --> 01:35.111
(SINGS TUNE IN IRISH GAELIC)

01:38.307 --> 01:39.699
(REPEATS TUNE)

01:40.225 --> 01:41.325
(CHUCKLES)

01:42.186 --> 01:44.755
Bedtime. Finish up, you two.

01:44.855 --> 01:46.956
Dad, look at the selkie.

01:47.524 --> 01:49.551
- Look.
- Oh.

01:49.651 --> 01:51.220
BEN: She's singing her song

01:51.320 --> 01:54.922
so that she can send all the fairies
home across the sea.

01:55.365 --> 01:58.593
And look, look,
she's turning into a seal.

01:58.702 --> 02:00.187
Do you like the selkie?

02:00.287 --> 02:01.271
She's beautiful.

02:01.371 --> 02:03.941
But we have to finish it
before the baby comes.

02:04.041 --> 02:06.559
We have lots of time to finish it, Ben.

02:06.668 --> 02:07.861
But it's time to sleep now.

02:07.961 --> 02:09.061
Okay.

02:11.882 --> 02:13.566
- (CU BARKING)
- Cu, good boy.

02:14.134 --> 02:15.443
(LAUGHS)

02:16.345 --> 02:17.329
(GASPS)

02:17.429 --> 02:18.414
Are you all right?

02:18.514 --> 02:20.823
I'm fine. It's fine.

02:22.059 --> 02:23.326
- Comfy?
- Mmm-hmm.

02:24.019 --> 02:27.997
Now, settle down.
There's something I want to give you.

02:28.732 --> 02:31.083
(PLAYING TUNE)

02:36.573 --> 02:38.308
(GASPS) What is it?

02:38.408 --> 02:42.386
This is an ancient shell that my mother
gave me a long time ago.

02:43.080 --> 02:45.681
Hold it to your ear
and listen carefully.

02:46.208 --> 02:48.851
You'll hear the song of the sea.

02:49.002 --> 02:50.102
(GASPS)

02:50.712 --> 02:52.855
- I can hear the sea.
- (CHUCKLES)

02:54.383 --> 02:55.942
Keep listening.

02:57.177 --> 02:59.153
(SINGING IN IRISH GAELIC)

03:05.102 --> 03:06.879
Mum?

03:06.979 --> 03:08.454
BRONACH: Yes?

03:08.939 --> 03:11.499
I can't wait for the baby to come.

03:12.025 --> 03:14.001
We're going to be
best friends, aren't we?

03:14.653 --> 03:16.128
Of course you are.

03:16.613 --> 03:19.966
You're going to be the best
big brother in the world.

03:22.077 --> 03:23.928
(SINGING IN IRISH GAELIC)

03:29.626 --> 03:30.726
(GROANING)

03:30.961 --> 03:32.070
CONOR: Bronach?

03:32.170 --> 03:33.197
BEN: Mum?

03:33.297 --> 03:34.397
I'm so sorry.

03:34.631 --> 03:35.773
CONOR: Bronach!

03:36.300 --> 03:37.566
Mum?

03:39.136 --> 03:40.403
Mum?

04:18.716 --> 04:20.608
(BEN SINGING)

04:26.808 --> 04:28.293
Here, Cu, look at this.

04:28.393 --> 04:30.212
Mum used to tell me the story.

04:30.312 --> 04:32.830
It's the giant Mac Lir and his dogs.

04:33.023 --> 04:34.331
They're best friends, like us.

04:40.030 --> 04:43.215
Cu, don't go too close to the water,
it's dangerous.

04:48.705 --> 04:50.514
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

04:52.626 --> 04:54.444
For someone who hasn't
learned how to talk,

04:54.544 --> 04:56.103
you are really loud.

04:57.130 --> 04:59.231
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

04:59.841 --> 05:01.493
Oh, come on, Saoirse!

05:01.593 --> 05:02.619
Why don't you go down there

05:02.719 --> 05:05.654
and play with some rocks, or something?
(GRUNTING)

05:06.223 --> 05:07.323
(GASPS)

05:08.225 --> 05:09.617
(CU BARKING)

05:16.400 --> 05:19.251
Hey, Cu, I'm drawing
the Great Seanachai.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.045
(BEN LAUGHING)

05:21.238 --> 05:23.672
- He has loads of hair, like you.
- (BARKS)

05:47.931 --> 05:49.031
(BARKING)

05:49.599 --> 05:50.699
Ugh.

05:51.268 --> 05:53.045
Dad said I'm in charge

05:53.145 --> 05:55.204
and I say there's no going in the water.

05:57.399 --> 05:59.291
It's dangerous.

05:59.943 --> 06:01.377
- I can't.
- (BARKING LOUDLY)

06:03.447 --> 06:05.214
Cu, I can't!

06:09.077 --> 06:10.177
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

06:10.454 --> 06:11.438
(SCREAMS)

06:11.538 --> 06:12.680
Cu, no!

06:13.373 --> 06:14.473
Whoa!

06:14.708 --> 06:16.433
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

06:17.043 --> 06:18.310
No!

06:21.465 --> 06:22.565
(GASPING)

06:33.268 --> 06:34.368
(COUGHING)

06:34.936 --> 06:38.340
BEN: That's it!
I'm not looking after you anymore.

06:38.440 --> 06:40.050
You nearly got me killed.

06:40.150 --> 06:42.585
Come out, with your hands up!

06:54.664 --> 06:55.931
(SHIP HORN BLOWING)

07:01.505 --> 07:03.731
BEN: Don't turn around, keep going.

07:04.424 --> 07:06.191
(SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

07:17.729 --> 07:19.589
Dad, she went into the water

07:19.689 --> 07:21.081
and nearly got me killed!

07:21.274 --> 07:24.511
Just because it's her birthday,
she thinks she can do whatever she likes.

07:24.611 --> 07:28.547
You'd better give it to her this time
'cause I'm not minding her anymore.

07:28.782 --> 07:30.424
Dad!

07:30.700 --> 07:32.968
What? Are you playing cops 'n' robbers?

07:33.286 --> 07:34.929
Are you going to give out to her?

07:35.038 --> 07:37.348
Ah! Here's the birthday girl.

07:37.958 --> 07:39.516
Come up here to me.

07:40.085 --> 07:41.236
Dad!

07:41.336 --> 07:43.405
You were under arrest, were you?

07:43.505 --> 07:44.813
Dad?

08:01.731 --> 08:03.457
(SHIP HORN BLOWING IN DISTANCE)

08:10.949 --> 08:14.551
Are you here for the birthday party
at the lighthouse today?

08:14.953 --> 08:17.471
Young Saoirse is six, is she?

08:18.957 --> 08:20.432
(MUFFLED SPEECH)

08:27.674 --> 08:29.858
Well, you old witch.

08:30.719 --> 08:31.944
(CAR HONKING HORN)

08:32.095 --> 08:33.529
Ugh! Granny.

08:35.682 --> 08:37.292
She's going to try and make us

08:37.392 --> 08:39.034
move to the city again, isn't she?

08:43.273 --> 08:46.709
I don't know how you can live
in this awful place.

08:48.361 --> 08:50.587
- You children are a state.
- (PARROT SQUAWKS)

08:54.784 --> 08:57.219
Is that your birthday outfit?

08:58.496 --> 09:00.556
Haven't you learnt to speak yet?

09:01.166 --> 09:03.434
The doctors said she
will in her own time.

09:03.585 --> 09:04.685
Hmph.

09:04.836 --> 09:07.614
The child can't be dressed
like that on her birthday.

09:07.714 --> 09:09.148
It's a disgrace!

09:12.469 --> 09:13.954
Put this on.

09:14.054 --> 09:15.997
Little girls only turn six once.

09:16.097 --> 09:18.741
And they need to be properly dressed.

09:19.392 --> 09:22.036
Now, isn't that lovely?

09:22.479 --> 09:25.080
Don't move now, until I call you.

09:27.442 --> 09:28.542
(SIGHS)

09:46.336 --> 09:47.436
(GASPS)

10:05.814 --> 10:07.340
- (INHALES DEEPLY)
- BEN: No, that's mine!

10:07.440 --> 10:09.625
Mum gave it to me, not you!

10:10.694 --> 10:11.794
CONOR: Ben!

10:13.655 --> 10:14.880
She's stealing from me again.

10:16.199 --> 10:17.934
She's nothing but a dirty stealer.

10:18.034 --> 10:19.686
I don't want to hear it.

10:19.786 --> 10:20.896
GRANNY: Saoirse!

10:20.996 --> 10:22.429
Your granny wants you downstairs.

10:22.539 --> 10:23.639
(GROANING)

10:28.211 --> 10:34.242
Now, Saoirse, try some of my nettle tea
and gooseberry buns there.

10:34.342 --> 10:36.568
Very good for the voice.

10:37.470 --> 10:39.071
It might cure you.

10:51.276 --> 10:56.139
Now, everybody ready for Saoirse
to blow out the candles, eh?

10:56.239 --> 10:59.007
I want to capture
the emotion of the day.

10:59.284 --> 11:01.385
One big, happy family.

11:01.745 --> 11:03.980
Smile on the count of three.

11:04.080 --> 11:05.389
Ready?

11:05.790 --> 11:07.182
- (INHALES DEEPLY)
- One,

11:07.917 --> 11:09.685
two,

11:10.420 --> 11:11.613
- three!
- Ahh!

11:11.713 --> 11:12.813
(CAMERA CLICKING)

11:13.423 --> 11:14.699
GRANNY: You little terror!

11:14.799 --> 11:16.400
- CONOR: Ben!
- (DOOR CLOSES)

11:17.385 --> 11:18.578
(GRANNY SINGING IN DISTANCE)

11:18.678 --> 11:21.572
Believe me, life is better as a dog, Cu.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.907
Stupid Saoirse, stupid birthdays.

11:24.184 --> 11:25.835
- (BARKS)
- (LAUGHS)

11:25.935 --> 11:27.870
You'll always be my best friend.

11:32.025 --> 11:33.584
- (GRANNY HUMMING)
- The kids are in bed.

11:33.860 --> 11:36.420
I'm just heading over to the mainland
for one with Dan.

11:36.613 --> 11:39.715
You're better off not thinking
about that night, you know.

11:40.450 --> 11:43.218
Her anniversary is
just once a year, Mum.

12:03.890 --> 12:05.449
What do you want?

12:05.683 --> 12:07.201
You want a story?

12:08.978 --> 12:11.622
Hmm. Okay, I'll tell you a story.

12:12.273 --> 12:15.292
Did you ever hear of
Macha the Owl Witch?

12:15.443 --> 12:16.543
(INHALES SHARPLY)

12:16.820 --> 12:18.471
Well, she's evil.

12:18.571 --> 12:20.255
You know the island out at sea?

12:20.865 --> 12:22.716
It's called Mac Lir.

12:22.909 --> 12:26.970
It's called that because it's not
an island at all, it's a huge giant.

12:28.581 --> 12:32.184
Macha's owls took all the giant's feelings
and turned him to stone.

12:32.752 --> 12:34.269
And do you know the worst of it?

12:34.629 --> 12:37.022
- She was his mother!
- (SAOIRSE GASPS)

12:37.549 --> 12:41.360
He was her first victim
and she hasn't stopped since.

12:41.511 --> 12:45.040
To this day, all the fairies are afraid
to come out on Halloween night

12:45.140 --> 12:48.251
because if they do,
Macha's owls will find them

12:48.351 --> 12:50.911
and take their feelings
and turn them to stone.

12:51.563 --> 12:53.256
Tomorrow is Halloween.

12:53.356 --> 12:55.175
Macha's owls might even come here

12:55.275 --> 12:58.252
and take Dad's feelings
and turn him to stone!

12:58.611 --> 13:00.837
And then nobody would love you.

13:01.030 --> 13:03.600
And this is what Macha looks like.

13:03.700 --> 13:05.676
(HOOTING)

13:06.244 --> 13:07.928
(CACKLING EVILLY)

13:11.708 --> 13:12.975
(WHIMPERS)

13:14.711 --> 13:16.853
Saoirse, it's just one of Mum's stories.

13:17.005 --> 13:18.355
It's not real.

13:34.731 --> 13:36.373
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

13:44.240 --> 13:45.632
(CU SNORING)

13:58.963 --> 13:59.948
(TOOTS)

14:00.048 --> 14:01.148
(GASPS)

14:07.722 --> 14:09.031
(SOFT TOOTS)

14:17.523 --> 14:18.623
(GASPS)

14:33.957 --> 14:35.182
(GASPS)

15:32.265 --> 15:33.365
(GASPS)

16:36.662 --> 16:37.804
(GASPS)

17:00.478 --> 17:01.953
(SEALS BARKING)

17:03.606 --> 17:05.248
(IMITATES BARKING)

18:15.052 --> 18:16.820
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

18:27.607 --> 18:28.707
(GASPS)

18:39.535 --> 18:41.261
(LOW RUMBLING)

18:47.919 --> 18:49.019
(SNORING)

18:49.712 --> 18:50.812
(GASPS)

18:53.966 --> 18:56.026
GRANNY: Saoirse!

19:00.765 --> 19:02.324
Saoirse!

19:10.608 --> 19:11.708
(GRANNY GASPS)

19:12.276 --> 19:13.710
The child.

19:22.745 --> 19:23.771
(GRUNTING)

19:23.871 --> 19:25.639
Oh, my gosh. Oh, my good...

19:26.874 --> 19:29.193
This is the last straw now.

19:29.293 --> 19:33.104
I'll not have any more of this
wild carry-on. No more of it!

19:34.423 --> 19:35.408
(SAOIRSE COUGHS)

19:35.508 --> 19:38.526
Now look, you've caught a cold.

19:41.222 --> 19:42.832
Did you know she was up?

19:42.932 --> 19:44.199
- Wha...
- CONOR: What's wrong?

19:44.308 --> 19:45.835
GRANNY: I found her washed up

19:45.935 --> 19:48.453
on the shore in the middle of the night.

19:48.688 --> 19:51.048
She's not safe in this awful place.

19:51.148 --> 19:53.124
- I know what's best.
- CONOR: Hold on a second, Mum.

19:53.276 --> 19:55.845
No, you hold on. Where were you?

19:55.945 --> 19:58.463
Off in the pub with that
old fool of a ferryman.

19:58.698 --> 20:01.017
This is no place for children, Conor,

20:01.117 --> 20:02.810
this is no place for a family.

20:02.910 --> 20:04.844
That's the end of it now.

20:05.538 --> 20:07.597
(SOBBING) I need to take my medicine.

20:10.876 --> 20:12.394
Oh, Saoirse.

20:14.630 --> 20:16.898
BEN: Dad, where did she get this?

20:19.468 --> 20:20.860
Give me that.

20:26.892 --> 20:27.992
(COUGHS)

20:36.736 --> 20:38.586
I can't lose her, too, Bronach.

21:25.576 --> 21:27.135
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

21:31.666 --> 21:33.183
- (DOOR OPENS)
- (GASPS)

21:39.340 --> 21:40.940
Stubborn boy.

21:41.550 --> 21:45.288
I'm not going. You can't make me.

21:45.388 --> 21:47.790
I know what's best for you.

21:47.890 --> 21:49.375
So, you'd better stop this nonsense

21:49.475 --> 21:51.659
at once and do what you're told.

21:53.813 --> 21:57.300
BEN: It's not fair.
Please, at least let me take Cu.

21:57.400 --> 21:58.426
(WHIMPERING)

21:58.526 --> 21:59.552
I don't want to go!

21:59.652 --> 22:00.678
- (GRUNTING)
- Be quiet, Ben.

22:00.778 --> 22:03.087
Get in the car and stop
all this carry-on.

22:04.240 --> 22:06.642
BEN: Dad! Dad, tell her I won't go.

22:06.742 --> 22:09.719
Please, Dad? I'm staying with you.

22:10.287 --> 22:11.846
Dad.

22:13.582 --> 22:17.028
No, Dad, no!
It's Saoirse's fault, not mine.

22:17.128 --> 22:20.355
Why do I have to go? Don't make me go!

22:20.881 --> 22:23.525
- Let me out!
- Stop it, Ben! Will you?

22:25.386 --> 22:26.903
(SOBBING SOFTLY)

22:28.055 --> 22:29.155
(SNIFFLING)

22:29.932 --> 22:31.032
(SIGHS)

22:31.350 --> 22:32.909
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

22:39.734 --> 22:41.751
Dad?

22:41.944 --> 22:43.054
Dad!

22:43.154 --> 22:44.629
(CU BARKING)

23:16.312 --> 23:17.412
Cu!

23:18.272 --> 23:19.747
(SHIP HORN BLOWING)

23:21.317 --> 23:23.501
BEN:
Stay away from the water, you'll drown.

23:23.903 --> 23:25.837
I'll come back for you, I promise.

23:26.238 --> 23:27.338
(WHIMPERING)

23:30.659 --> 23:32.260
(BEN SOBBING)

23:34.497 --> 23:36.556
What's the matter with you, Ben?

23:37.416 --> 23:40.059
Granny wouldn't let Cu come with us.

23:41.962 --> 23:44.073
Ah, the old witch.

23:44.173 --> 23:45.732
(SEALS WHINING)

23:46.967 --> 23:48.443
Would you look at that?

23:49.094 --> 23:51.487
Look, Ben, seals.

23:53.724 --> 23:56.868
There haven't been seals
around here for years.

24:22.837 --> 24:23.937
(WHIMPERING)

25:00.583 --> 25:01.609
(CRYING SOFTLY)

25:01.709 --> 25:06.104
GRANNY: Ben, there will be no tears
in this car, or in my house.

25:06.547 --> 25:08.189
Do you hear me, Ben?

25:09.091 --> 25:12.328
The city is no place
for a dog of Cu's size.

25:12.428 --> 25:15.196
He'd only be whimpering
and whining there.

25:15.681 --> 25:18.199
You wouldn't want that
for him now, would you?

25:19.018 --> 25:20.118
(SIGHS)

25:21.353 --> 25:25.039
GRANNY: You will love it
in the city, Ben, I know you will.

26:15.991 --> 26:17.425
(CARS HORNS HONKING)

26:22.206 --> 26:23.598
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

26:33.425 --> 26:35.068
(WARBLING SINGING ON RADIO)

26:39.515 --> 26:40.782
(SIGHS)

26:42.643 --> 26:45.369
Oh, isn't this nice? I love this song.

26:45.688 --> 26:47.121
(HUMMING)

26:53.988 --> 26:55.505
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON HEADPHONES)

26:56.865 --> 26:59.101
Our bathroom's upstairs, dear.

26:59.201 --> 27:02.220
Don't use the good towels,
they're only for guests.

27:03.455 --> 27:05.223
(GRANNY CONTINUES HUMMING)

27:14.466 --> 27:15.691
(GASPS)

27:26.937 --> 27:28.746
- (WARBLING SINGING CONTINUES)
- (CONTINUES HUMMING)

27:30.232 --> 27:31.916
(PLAYING TUNE)

27:48.709 --> 27:50.101
(OWLS HOOTING)

27:52.463 --> 27:54.021
(HUMMING ALONG TO RADIO)

27:55.090 --> 27:56.190
Ohh!

28:02.264 --> 28:04.490
(ROCK MUSIC BLARING ON HEADPHONES)

28:07.102 --> 28:08.494
- (GRANNY SCREAMING)
- Huh?

28:09.354 --> 28:10.872
(SHOWER RUNNING)

28:13.609 --> 28:15.710
GRANNY: My best coat.

28:22.868 --> 28:24.218
(COUGHING)

28:24.536 --> 28:26.971
(SIGHS) It's not even 4:00.

28:28.123 --> 28:30.391
No-one goes to bed at this time.

28:30.751 --> 28:33.811
Look at that now,
it is completely ruined.

28:34.296 --> 28:35.563
(CHILDREN SHOUTING)

28:35.964 --> 28:38.900
Goodness gracious,
have they no homes to go to?

28:39.301 --> 28:40.401
Ooh!

28:41.136 --> 28:42.695
It's not safe.

28:44.598 --> 28:45.708
What the...

28:45.808 --> 28:46.908
Are you the selkie?

28:47.309 --> 28:48.877
Get out of that, will you?

28:48.977 --> 28:50.921
Little devils, go on, out with you.

28:51.021 --> 28:52.663
Go, before I ring the police!

28:55.025 --> 28:56.918
(MUTTERING)

28:57.653 --> 28:58.920
SPUD: Quick, get the coat.

29:00.030 --> 29:02.089
- The selkie coat.
- (GASPS)

29:09.581 --> 29:10.973
BEN: I'm coming to get you, Cu.

29:19.842 --> 29:21.651
(CHILDREN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

29:34.189 --> 29:35.924
Would you say that could be her?

29:36.024 --> 29:37.667
Could be. Come on.

29:40.821 --> 29:42.139
(OWLS HOOTING)

29:42.239 --> 29:43.631
(BELL TOLLING)

29:52.291 --> 29:53.891
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

29:54.293 --> 29:56.686
(SIGHS) What do you think you're doing?

29:58.505 --> 30:01.158
No. I'm going home to live with Cu.

30:01.258 --> 30:03.619
You're going to stay at Granny's.

30:03.719 --> 30:05.319
I said no!

30:06.221 --> 30:07.321
Ow!

30:08.891 --> 30:10.574
Right, that's it.

30:18.775 --> 30:22.503
You can only come with me
if you obey my orders at all times.

30:23.280 --> 30:25.307
I'm the oldest and that's the rule.

30:25.407 --> 30:28.143
If you put one step
out of line, I do this...

30:28.243 --> 30:29.635
(LINE REELING IN)

30:32.206 --> 30:33.190
(PLAYING TUNE)

30:33.290 --> 30:37.184
Hey! You stealer, that's mine.
Give it back.

30:38.086 --> 30:39.353
(SNEEZES)

30:39.671 --> 30:42.231
Ew! You're so disgusting.

30:44.051 --> 30:45.828
Okay, you can keep it for now,

30:45.928 --> 30:48.362
but you'd better clean it
when we get home.

30:50.599 --> 30:51.907
(PLAYING TUNE)

30:52.267 --> 30:53.701
(OWLS HOOTING)

30:55.687 --> 30:57.413
Hey. Excuse me?

30:58.106 --> 31:00.207
Maybe a bus driver could tell us.

31:13.372 --> 31:15.056
Wow.

31:17.626 --> 31:19.560
Look at this, Saoirse.

31:20.254 --> 31:21.354
(LAUGHING)

31:24.299 --> 31:25.826
Holy moly!

31:25.926 --> 31:27.818
Quick, Saoirse, help me catch it!

31:28.553 --> 31:30.446
(PLAYING TUNE)

31:33.934 --> 31:36.619
We've found her,
Lug, we've found her. At last!

31:36.937 --> 31:39.173
- Don't worry, selkie, we have your coat.
- Huh?

31:39.273 --> 31:42.625
- Come with us.
- Quick, lads, get the selkie to the fort.

31:42.859 --> 31:44.052
Before the owls spot us.

31:44.152 --> 31:45.252
(LINE REELING AWAY)

31:45.904 --> 31:48.255
Wait! No!

31:50.158 --> 31:51.550
Wait!

31:55.122 --> 31:56.222
(BEN SCREAMS)

31:57.332 --> 31:58.400
Where are we going?

31:58.500 --> 31:59.600
Ahhh!

31:59.918 --> 32:01.852
- (HORN HONKING)
- Whoa!

32:02.296 --> 32:03.604
Whoa! Whoa!

32:04.339 --> 32:05.439
- (CAR HORN HONKING)
- (SCREAMING)

32:27.988 --> 32:29.264
(SPUD LAUGHING)

32:29.364 --> 32:31.549
LUG: Lads, what a night.

32:32.326 --> 32:34.718
Not only did we find the selkie coat,

32:35.078 --> 32:36.980
but we found the selkie herself.

32:37.080 --> 32:38.273
Hooray!

32:38.373 --> 32:39.640
- (LAUGHS)
- Hooray!

32:39.875 --> 32:40.975
- LUG: Yoo-hoo!
- Huh?

32:42.127 --> 32:44.613
Now, before the selkie sings her
song to send us home,

32:44.713 --> 32:47.440
we should entertain her
with a few of our own tunes.

32:47.591 --> 32:50.744
- So, lads, your choice. Who'll get us started.
- SPUD: Here, Lug?

32:50.844 --> 32:52.736
I'll sing. (CLEARS THROAT)

32:52.929 --> 32:54.706
No, Spud, we want to keep the mood up

32:54.806 --> 32:55.948
before the main event.

32:56.058 --> 32:57.084
Isn't that right, selkie?

32:57.184 --> 32:58.951
I'll do my best, I promise.

33:00.062 --> 33:02.329
Give Mossy a go first, will you? Yoo!

33:02.564 --> 33:04.258
(PLAYING UPBEAT MUSIC)

33:04.358 --> 33:06.134
(SINGING) The selkie song is bright

33:06.234 --> 33:07.960
To waken all who follow

33:08.236 --> 33:12.099
Manannan will lead
and Tir Na Nog will follow

33:12.199 --> 33:16.103
ALL: Do-la-mon, a-pena pwee
Do-la-mon, manuela

33:16.203 --> 33:17.896
Do-la-mon, a-paricka

33:17.996 --> 33:19.982
Par-a-fee a-nerin

33:20.082 --> 33:21.024
(ALL LAUGHING)

33:21.124 --> 33:22.975
Lovely job, Mossy!

33:23.126 --> 33:24.852
Do you hear the lad's tune?

33:27.005 --> 33:28.105
Yoo-hoo!

33:28.715 --> 33:30.399
Right, who's next?

33:31.468 --> 33:33.944
Here, Lug, here. I'll sing.

33:34.304 --> 33:35.779
Oh. Go on, so.

33:35.889 --> 33:37.749
Tell us your name, selkie.

33:37.849 --> 33:40.242
So we can sing of your adventure.

33:40.435 --> 33:42.203
(SIGHS) Her name's Saoirse.

33:46.274 --> 33:48.209
Saoirse! Yoo!

33:48.777 --> 33:52.546
(SINGING) Saoirse the selkie
will sing and save the day

33:52.739 --> 33:56.393
The day that she who rescued her
will cheer and celebrate

33:56.493 --> 34:00.346
ALL: Oh, do-la-mon, a-pena pwee
Do-la-mon, manuela

34:00.455 --> 34:01.639
Do-la-mon...

34:03.125 --> 34:04.517
(OWLS HOOTING)

34:05.252 --> 34:08.530
Wait! I've forgotten the last verse.

34:08.630 --> 34:10.438
How did I manage that?

34:10.757 --> 34:13.900
BEN: (SINGING) Long, long we prayed
to hear the selkie song

34:14.261 --> 34:17.121
And now we pray again
that her song will never end

34:17.222 --> 34:18.581
Ha-ha! Yoo!

34:18.681 --> 34:21.033
That's it! Which one of you had it?

34:22.936 --> 34:25.130
Never mind. Keep the crack going, lads.

34:25.230 --> 34:28.925
ALL: (SINGING) Do-la-mon, a-pena pwee
Do-la-mon, manuela

34:29.025 --> 34:32.503
Do-la mon la faricka faralee a-nerin

34:34.114 --> 34:37.882
Now, lads, what you've
all been waiting for.

34:38.326 --> 34:40.978
Time for the selkie to
sing her lovely song.

34:41.079 --> 34:43.389
You'll be free soon, lads!

34:43.831 --> 34:46.400
The selkie song will send us all home.

34:46.501 --> 34:48.320
Wait, wait, will you?

34:48.420 --> 34:50.072
Come on, now, selkie, sing it.

34:50.172 --> 34:51.605
Does she know the words?

34:51.840 --> 34:53.658
Give her a chance,
give her a chance, will you?

34:53.757 --> 34:55.034
Her coat.

34:55.135 --> 34:56.944
(LAUGHING) I almost forgot.

34:57.094 --> 34:58.622
Aren't I some eejit?

34:58.722 --> 35:01.750
How was I expecting the selkie
to sing without her coat?

35:01.850 --> 35:02.950
(INHALES DEEPLY)

35:03.894 --> 35:04.994
(SNEEZES)

35:05.520 --> 35:08.382
- What's wrong?
- I don't think it's the right coat.

35:08.482 --> 35:10.124
Oh, no.

35:10.859 --> 35:13.752
She can't sing. She can't even talk.

35:14.196 --> 35:16.139
A human child!

35:16.239 --> 35:18.225
You're the one that
gave me the last verse.

35:18.325 --> 35:19.393
(MOSSY AND SPUD GASPS)

35:19.493 --> 35:21.520
Yeah, my mother used to sing it.

35:21.620 --> 35:23.387
She said it was a fairy song.

35:23.497 --> 35:24.481
That'd be right.

35:24.581 --> 35:25.607
So that would make you...

35:25.707 --> 35:27.317
We prefer to call ourselves...

35:27.417 --> 35:28.443
The Other Crowd.

35:28.543 --> 35:30.946
- The Good Names.
- The Deenashee.

35:31.046 --> 35:34.189
I can't believe it.
(LAUGHS) The Deenashee.

35:34.382 --> 35:36.400
That's what Mum called the fairies.

35:36.593 --> 35:39.704
You're actually real, not just stories.

35:39.804 --> 35:42.865
Human child, do you know
where the selkie's coat is?

35:43.350 --> 35:44.668
Her real coat.

35:44.768 --> 35:47.254
Yes, my father took it.
It's in our lighthouse.

35:47.354 --> 35:50.715
Do you hear that, lads? We are saved!

35:50.815 --> 35:52.050
- (WOOD CRACKING)
- Ahh!

35:52.150 --> 35:53.250
(GASPS)

35:56.571 --> 35:57.671
(OWLS HOOTING)

36:00.242 --> 36:02.769
Daggers out! Protect the selkie.

36:02.869 --> 36:04.011
(SCREECHING)

36:10.460 --> 36:11.560
Get away!

36:12.003 --> 36:13.155
Saoirse!

36:13.255 --> 36:14.355
LUG: Get back!

36:15.590 --> 36:16.899
No!

36:17.259 --> 36:18.817
- The selkie!
- LUG: No!

36:28.019 --> 36:29.119
LUG: No!

36:29.437 --> 36:30.579
Hold on!

36:31.856 --> 36:32.956
(BEN GRUNTING)

36:34.109 --> 36:35.209
(ALL GROANING)

36:39.364 --> 36:41.131
They're going for the selkie!

36:41.283 --> 36:42.591
Saoirse!

36:43.118 --> 36:44.227
Run!

36:44.327 --> 36:45.427
(SCREECHING)

36:45.704 --> 36:46.804
(THE DEENASHEE GRUNTING)

36:50.417 --> 36:51.934
Run away!

36:58.550 --> 37:01.036
Human child,
find the selkie's true coat,

37:01.136 --> 37:03.445
then she can sing the song
and save us all.

37:07.976 --> 37:09.243
(SCREECHING)

37:10.061 --> 37:11.495
(PLAYING TUNE)

37:18.153 --> 37:19.670
(THE DEENASHEE GASPING)

37:22.032 --> 37:23.507
(OWLS SCREECHING)

37:23.617 --> 37:26.635
Quickly, human child,
before the owls return.

37:26.786 --> 37:29.471
That pipe will see you
to the outside world. Go!

37:32.000 --> 37:34.402
SPUD: I'd like to sing some more.

37:34.502 --> 37:35.936
LUG: Ah. Go on so.

37:36.671 --> 37:39.773
SPUD: (SINGING) Do-la-mon, a-pena pwee,
Do-la-mon...

37:45.430 --> 37:46.822
There's a bus.

37:47.641 --> 37:48.991
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

37:51.645 --> 37:53.412
Quick, Saoirse.

37:55.690 --> 37:57.583
I just saw real fairies.

37:57.776 --> 37:59.636
Course you did.
Sure haven't I been ferrying

37:59.736 --> 38:01.628
a lot of witches and goblins around.

38:01.988 --> 38:03.630
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

38:04.199 --> 38:05.475
Where are you going?

38:05.575 --> 38:06.967
Can you take us there?

38:07.702 --> 38:09.104
Uh... Well, let me see now...

38:09.204 --> 38:11.773
I can take you as far as Clonmellon.

38:11.873 --> 38:13.984
You might have to wait
for one or two hours,

38:14.084 --> 38:18.395
then get the feeder bus,
but that only runs in the mornings.

38:18.713 --> 38:21.032
Ah, sure. You know,
you'll get there eventually.

38:21.132 --> 38:22.117
(SIGHS)

38:22.217 --> 38:23.817
Okay, two tickets, please.

38:29.140 --> 38:30.699
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

38:32.394 --> 38:36.163
Those stories that Mum told me,
they're all true.

38:36.815 --> 38:38.332
Are you really a...

38:39.150 --> 38:40.667
...selkie?

38:43.655 --> 38:45.756
Oh, genie mackerel.

39:01.881 --> 39:03.732
(WOMAN HUMMING)

39:11.850 --> 39:13.659
(SAOIRSE PLAYING TUNE ON SHELL)

39:30.618 --> 39:33.637
What are you doing? We're on the bus!

39:34.289 --> 39:35.889
I'm getting us home.

39:38.918 --> 39:40.185
(TIRES SCREECHING)

39:40.295 --> 39:41.395
(CHILDREN SCREAMING)

39:43.840 --> 39:46.242
You should've said if you
wanted to get off the bus!

39:46.342 --> 39:48.402
This is not an official stop, you know.

39:48.803 --> 39:50.362
Bleedin' trick or treaters.

39:57.645 --> 40:00.548
Great, just great. Now what do we do?

40:00.648 --> 40:02.499
(TOOTS)

40:03.818 --> 40:05.929
Oh, right, let's follow
the magical lights.

40:06.029 --> 40:08.297
That's much safer than being on a bus.

40:13.369 --> 40:14.803
(GATE CREAKING)

40:23.838 --> 40:25.772
(PLAYING TUNE)

40:53.034 --> 40:54.436
Some of these could be fairies

40:54.536 --> 40:57.471
turned to stone,
like the ones in the roundabout.

41:01.042 --> 41:03.060
There he is.

41:04.212 --> 41:05.812
(PLAYING TUNE)

41:07.006 --> 41:08.106
(CROWS CAWING)

41:12.971 --> 41:15.999
Stop. Those lights drew the fairies

41:16.099 --> 41:18.075
to us and maybe the owls, too.

41:19.352 --> 41:22.412
Don't play the shell anymore,
it's too dangerous.

41:22.522 --> 41:23.882
I can get us home using my map.

41:23.982 --> 41:26.083
Just you wait and see.

41:30.905 --> 41:33.006
This is the way, I know it.

41:39.914 --> 41:41.014
(GRUNTING)

41:53.761 --> 41:55.612
We're not lost, no way.

41:57.599 --> 42:00.867
If we find a better spot,
I might be able to see the mountains.

42:00.977 --> 42:02.369
Then I'll know the right way.

42:06.065 --> 42:07.582
We're not lost.

42:08.276 --> 42:10.043
(PLAYING TUNE)

42:10.862 --> 42:12.879
(SIGHS) What did I say
about playing that?

42:14.073 --> 42:17.310
If those owls come back,
I'm going to let them take you.

42:17.410 --> 42:18.719
(FAINT GROWLING)

42:19.621 --> 42:20.887
(SOFTLY) What's that?

42:21.456 --> 42:22.556
(GROWLING)

42:24.375 --> 42:26.101
(SOFTLY) Don't let it be Macha.

42:27.503 --> 42:29.229
Please, don't let it be Macha.

42:32.967 --> 42:34.776
Saoirse, get down.

42:36.179 --> 42:37.455
(BARKING)

42:37.555 --> 42:38.655
Whoo-hoo!

42:39.349 --> 42:40.699
Cu!

42:40.808 --> 42:42.576
Come here, boy, come here!

42:44.479 --> 42:46.621
Okay, okay, get off me.

42:48.232 --> 42:50.125
Oh, Cu, you found us.

42:51.694 --> 42:55.390
Wait, if Cu found us here
and he's come all this way on his own,

42:55.490 --> 42:57.591
he can surely get us back home.

43:01.746 --> 43:02.846
(CU BARKS)

43:04.248 --> 43:06.016
Take us home, Cu.

43:16.135 --> 43:17.611
(SHEEP BLEATING)

43:34.696 --> 43:36.880
We've a long way to go, you know.

43:39.659 --> 43:40.759
(COUGHING)

43:55.550 --> 43:57.651
What's happening to you?

43:59.303 --> 44:00.403
(BEN GRUNTING)

44:21.784 --> 44:23.426
Look, the mountains!

44:27.790 --> 44:28.890
(CU BARKING)

44:33.212 --> 44:35.105
We can't keep going like this.

44:38.885 --> 44:42.028
It'll be dry there.
Giddy-up, Cu. Come on.

44:49.479 --> 44:50.579
(WHIMPERING)

44:57.862 --> 45:00.088
(SOFTLY) Jesus, Mary and Joseph.

45:00.198 --> 45:01.965
Come on, get on my back.

45:12.460 --> 45:13.560
(COWS MOOING)

45:16.839 --> 45:18.773
Oh, no, stinging nettles.

45:19.675 --> 45:22.745
Keep your legs up, Saoirse.
These plants sting pretty bad.

45:22.845 --> 45:23.913
Ow!

45:24.013 --> 45:25.113
Ahh!

45:38.277 --> 45:39.262
(GROANS)

45:39.362 --> 45:41.087
(SOFTLY) Stupid nettles.

45:49.705 --> 45:52.641
I'm just after getting you
out of the rain, you know.

46:11.185 --> 46:13.119
Dock leaves!

46:14.188 --> 46:15.789
Good thinking, Saoirse.

46:22.780 --> 46:24.673
That feels way better.

46:25.616 --> 46:27.133
Thanks.

46:37.879 --> 46:40.021
(PLAYING TUNE)

47:00.943 --> 47:02.794
I drew this holy well on my map,

47:02.904 --> 47:05.005
I knew it. We're on the right track.

47:13.623 --> 47:15.775
There'd better not be any snot on it.

47:15.875 --> 47:16.975
(CHUCKLES)

47:18.085 --> 47:20.645
When the rain stops,
we can get going again.

47:22.298 --> 47:24.399
Hmm. Maybe we can take a short cut.

47:25.301 --> 47:26.577
- (CU BARKS)
- Saoirse?

47:26.677 --> 47:27.703
- (RUNNING FOOTSTEPS)
- (WATER SPLASHING)

47:27.803 --> 47:28.903
(CU BARKING)

47:30.223 --> 47:31.531
Saoirse!

47:34.477 --> 47:35.869
Come up, come up!

47:37.230 --> 47:38.913
She's not coming up.

47:40.608 --> 47:41.833
(BARKING)

47:43.194 --> 47:45.587
I can't. I can't do it,
I just can't do it.

47:47.990 --> 47:49.267
I can't.

47:49.367 --> 47:50.810
No, no, no, no!

47:50.910 --> 47:52.010
Ahhh!

47:57.750 --> 47:58.850
(MOOS)

47:59.877 --> 48:01.227
(MUFFLED SCREAM)

48:18.062 --> 48:19.162
(GASPING)

48:20.481 --> 48:21.748
Saoirse!

48:22.316 --> 48:23.541
Cu!

48:25.319 --> 48:26.419
(COUGHING)

48:38.165 --> 48:40.809
Okay, okay, okay.

48:42.378 --> 48:43.603
Okay.

48:55.641 --> 48:57.534
Saoirse!

49:05.151 --> 49:06.835
Saoirse.

49:14.952 --> 49:16.386
(OWLS HOOTING)

49:45.900 --> 49:48.302
FAIRY: (SINGING) Do-le-mon, do le...

49:48.402 --> 49:50.221
Do-le-mon...

49:50.321 --> 49:52.422
Do, do-le-mon...

49:52.907 --> 49:54.340
(FAIRY GRUMBLING)

49:54.742 --> 49:56.310
Dooo-le...

49:56.410 --> 49:58.428
Ah! Now then, what is it?

50:00.623 --> 50:04.392
(SINGING) Do-la-mon, a-pena pwee
Do-la-mon, manuela

50:04.835 --> 50:05.935
Oh!

50:12.218 --> 50:13.318
(RUSTLING)

50:15.262 --> 50:16.863
(BOTH SCREAMING)

50:17.973 --> 50:19.458
How do you know that song?

50:19.558 --> 50:21.117
My mother taught it to me.

50:21.268 --> 50:24.422
And who are you, human child?

50:24.522 --> 50:25.830
I'm nobody.

50:26.482 --> 50:27.758
Nobody?

50:27.858 --> 50:29.542
(STAMMERING) I mean, I'm Ben.

50:29.819 --> 50:30.919
(SCREAMS)

50:31.695 --> 50:32.795
(GASPS)

50:33.781 --> 50:35.048
I'm looking for my sister.

50:36.534 --> 50:38.311
I lost her down here.

50:38.411 --> 50:39.511
Hmm.

50:40.704 --> 50:42.388
Look at that.

50:46.043 --> 50:49.395
I could do with a little
more light. Could you?

50:52.091 --> 50:53.983
(SPEAKING IRISH GAELIC)

50:56.429 --> 50:57.529
(LAUGHING)

51:19.076 --> 51:23.096
So good to see you again,
my little sulcha.

51:23.539 --> 51:25.682
Holy moly!

51:26.333 --> 51:27.433
(GASPS)

51:28.502 --> 51:29.602
(SCREAMING)

51:30.337 --> 51:31.437
Whoa!

51:35.009 --> 51:36.651
Who are you?

51:37.178 --> 51:39.288
I told you, I'm Ben.

51:39.388 --> 51:42.166
I'm just down here
looking for my sister.

51:42.266 --> 51:45.118
Oh, yes. That's right.

51:45.728 --> 51:48.047
Forgive me, I have no memory,

51:48.147 --> 51:50.758
except for what is in
these hairs, you see.

51:50.858 --> 51:51.958
Whoa!

51:53.027 --> 51:55.096
Is all of this growing out of you?

51:55.196 --> 51:56.588
It seems to be.

51:57.448 --> 51:59.299
Are you the Great Seanachai?

51:59.617 --> 52:00.717
Um...

52:02.536 --> 52:04.596
Yes. Yes!

52:05.039 --> 52:07.974
- Whoa!
- I am the Great Seanachai!

52:08.792 --> 52:10.184
I'd almost forgotten.

52:10.836 --> 52:12.822
My mum told me stories about you.

52:12.922 --> 52:14.698
Careful, lad.

52:14.798 --> 52:16.325
You could snap a hair,

52:16.425 --> 52:18.452
you'll lose the story of me forever.

52:18.552 --> 52:19.652
Whoa!

52:21.972 --> 52:24.532
Whoa, each hair holds a story?

52:25.226 --> 52:26.534
Does it?

52:26.894 --> 52:28.161
Oh, that's right.

52:28.771 --> 52:30.371
That's right.

52:30.689 --> 52:33.166
Show us one here and let's have a look.

52:35.069 --> 52:37.337
Now, let's see...

52:38.989 --> 52:42.383
- This is Mac Lir, the great giant.
- (CRYING)

52:44.328 --> 52:46.721
His heart was broken into pieces

52:46.914 --> 52:50.141
by a great, great tragedy.

52:51.460 --> 52:55.355
Such was his anguish
that he cried a whole ocean.

52:59.051 --> 53:01.996
Higher and higher, it rose

53:02.096 --> 53:05.031
until we were all sure
to drown in his tears.

53:07.434 --> 53:09.077
BEN: I know this.

53:11.105 --> 53:14.499
SEANACHAI: Macha sent her owls
to take his suffering away.

53:17.236 --> 53:18.336
(CRYING STOPS)

53:19.989 --> 53:22.057
BEN: And he was turned to stone.

53:22.157 --> 53:24.300
- SEANACHAI: That's right.
- (OWLS SCREECHING)

53:25.286 --> 53:28.054
A sad story by anyone's estimations.

53:29.164 --> 53:30.983
I've seen Macha's owls use those

53:31.083 --> 53:32.902
jars to turn the fairies to stone.

53:33.002 --> 53:34.894
And now they're after my sister.

53:35.129 --> 53:36.530
Can you help me?

53:36.630 --> 53:37.980
No.

53:38.382 --> 53:39.366
But...

53:39.466 --> 53:40.608
SEANACHAI: Well, you see now...

53:41.135 --> 53:43.329
I wouldn't have a clue
about human children.

53:43.429 --> 53:45.905
- BEN: Why?
- I only know about my own kind.

53:46.640 --> 53:48.876
But I think she is your kind.

53:48.976 --> 53:52.129
Or partly anyway.
The fairies said she was a selkie.

53:52.229 --> 53:53.329
- Ooh!
- Whoa!

53:53.814 --> 53:55.373
What did you say?

53:55.649 --> 53:57.843
A selkie? Really?

53:57.943 --> 53:59.637
Yeah, they were talking about a coat

53:59.737 --> 54:01.680
and a song and now I've lost her.

54:01.780 --> 54:03.589
Something is wrong.

54:04.158 --> 54:07.593
They've just been woken
and are already fading?

54:08.162 --> 54:09.262
Oh!

54:11.415 --> 54:12.608
Why?

54:12.708 --> 54:16.686
The sulcha and the selkie,
all of us are connected.

54:17.796 --> 54:19.522
This is not good.

54:20.007 --> 54:22.076
Something must've happened to her.

54:22.176 --> 54:23.869
That's what I'm trying to say.

54:23.969 --> 54:25.246
I lost her down here.

54:25.346 --> 54:26.956
Did the selkie have her coat with her?

54:27.056 --> 54:29.866
No, it's at home. My dad took it.

54:30.100 --> 54:31.200
(GROANS)

54:31.477 --> 54:34.838
Blasted humans! They don't have a clue.

54:34.938 --> 54:38.717
You must get the coat back to her.
Do you hear me?

54:38.817 --> 54:40.594
But I don't know where she is.

54:40.694 --> 54:42.754
Hold on a moment, laddie.

54:44.198 --> 54:48.384
Very few hairs still grow
because very few of us are left.

54:50.079 --> 54:54.056
But the selkie's, hers still grows.

54:55.292 --> 54:56.277
Hmm.

54:56.377 --> 54:58.487
That's her. That's when I lost her.

54:58.587 --> 55:00.614
Let's see what happens then.

55:00.714 --> 55:01.814
- (OWLS HOOTING)
- (GASPS)

55:03.008 --> 55:03.951
What's wrong?

55:04.051 --> 55:05.651
Macha has her now.

55:05.803 --> 55:08.821
She'll be turned to
stone soon, no doubt.

55:09.306 --> 55:13.168
You see, without her coat,
the selkie has no voice.

55:13.268 --> 55:16.547
And without her song,
she'll not last the night.

55:16.647 --> 55:18.966
And we'll all share in her fate.

55:19.066 --> 55:20.926
Oh, no. I've got to get out of here.

55:21.026 --> 55:22.177
I have to find her.

55:22.277 --> 55:24.555
Wait now. You still have a chance.

55:24.655 --> 55:25.755
(BEN SCREAMS)

55:28.075 --> 55:31.145
Follow this,
it will lead you through the tunnel.

55:31.245 --> 55:33.846
Mind, it won't be easy.

55:34.289 --> 55:36.015
Macha has lost all hope.

55:36.417 --> 55:39.393
And she will try and make you
lose hope, too.

55:41.630 --> 55:45.358
The selkie will not last long
beyond dawn without her coat.

55:48.637 --> 55:50.238
You must hurry.

55:51.098 --> 55:52.374
Okay.

55:52.474 --> 55:54.784
Oh. And be careful.

55:55.561 --> 55:57.203
Why? What's down there?

55:57.396 --> 55:58.496
Uh...

55:59.022 --> 56:00.665
(SINGING IN IRISH GAELIC)

56:06.739 --> 56:08.881
Lad go on with yourself.

56:11.827 --> 56:13.427
(SEANACHAI CONTINUES SINGING)

56:17.166 --> 56:18.192
SEANACHAI: Not bad.

56:18.292 --> 56:19.392
(SEANACHAI LAUGHS)

56:19.668 --> 56:20.736
Bye.

56:20.836 --> 56:23.229
(GASPS) Who said that?

57:10.177 --> 57:11.444
(WOMAN HUMMING)

57:16.850 --> 57:18.409
Mum.

57:22.815 --> 57:25.625
BEN: I can't wait for the baby to come.

57:26.068 --> 57:28.554
We're going to be
best friends, aren't we?

57:28.654 --> 57:31.964
You're going to be the best
big brother in the world.

57:41.208 --> 57:42.234
(GROANING)

57:42.334 --> 57:43.809
CONOR: Bronach?

57:44.545 --> 57:45.654
I'm so sorry.

57:45.754 --> 57:47.063
CONOR: Bronach?

57:47.548 --> 57:48.898
Mum?

57:58.725 --> 57:59.825
(GROANS)

58:06.859 --> 58:08.167
Bronach!

58:09.194 --> 58:10.503
Bronach!

58:10.779 --> 58:13.599
I've no more time,
I have to save our baby.

58:13.699 --> 58:14.850
CONOR: Bronach!

58:14.950 --> 58:16.175
I'm so sorry.

58:18.161 --> 58:19.512
Bronach!

58:20.789 --> 58:22.348
Bronach!

58:24.543 --> 58:25.643
(SCREAMING)

58:43.770 --> 58:44.870
(CU WHIMPERING)

58:45.105 --> 58:46.455
Dad?

58:48.734 --> 58:50.835
Dad, where's Mum?

58:51.486 --> 58:52.920
Where's Mum?

58:53.488 --> 58:55.756
- Dad?
- Say hello to Saoirse.

58:57.576 --> 58:59.677
This is your sister.

59:01.496 --> 59:03.472
You're her big brother.

59:03.832 --> 59:05.850
- (COOING)
- You must always look after her.

59:29.024 --> 59:30.750
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

59:54.841 --> 59:56.150
(OWLS HOOTING)

01:00:05.185 --> 01:00:06.545
Okay, okay.

01:00:06.645 --> 01:00:08.079
- FAIRY 1: Be careful!
- (EXCLAIMS)

01:00:08.772 --> 01:00:10.132
- FAIRY 2: Be brave!
- Ahh!

01:00:10.232 --> 01:00:14.710
Down here. Be careful in there.
Beware of the jars!

01:00:16.029 --> 01:00:17.129
(GRUNTING)

01:00:17.698 --> 01:00:18.765
Good luck.

01:00:18.865 --> 01:00:19.975
Be careful in there.

01:00:20.075 --> 01:00:21.801
- FAIRY 3: Watch it!
- FAIRY 4: The Owl Witch.

01:00:21.952 --> 01:00:24.021
- FAIRY 5: Good luck.
- FAIRY 6: Be careful.

01:00:24.121 --> 01:00:25.772
FAIRY 7: Mind her jars.

01:00:25.872 --> 01:00:27.556
FAIRY 8: The Owl Witch, beware!

01:00:40.470 --> 01:00:42.539
- FAIRY 9: Go safe.
- FAIRY 10: Mind yourself.

01:00:42.639 --> 01:00:44.740
- FAIRY 11: Mind yourself.
- FAIRY 12: Beware!

01:00:45.058 --> 01:00:47.159
(FAIRIES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

01:00:52.524 --> 01:00:53.833
Okay.

01:00:54.568 --> 01:00:55.668
(YELLING)

01:00:56.361 --> 01:00:58.087
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

01:01:01.324 --> 01:01:02.675
(LIGHTNING CRASHING)

01:01:08.749 --> 01:01:09.849
(WOMAN SIGHS)

01:01:19.092 --> 01:01:20.192
Ooh.

01:01:20.927 --> 01:01:25.698
You look wet and tired, human child.

01:01:26.767 --> 01:01:28.200
Macha?

01:01:29.269 --> 01:01:30.953
I am she.

01:01:32.105 --> 01:01:33.340
Really?

01:01:33.440 --> 01:01:36.834
The Owl Witch from the stories?

01:01:37.444 --> 01:01:38.878
- (OWLS HOOTING)
- (CHUCKLING SOFTLY)

01:01:39.112 --> 01:01:40.847
Well, now,

01:01:40.947 --> 01:01:44.383
those stories always
paint me as the bad one.

01:01:44.826 --> 01:01:46.927
But I'm not so terrible, you know.

01:01:47.454 --> 01:01:49.847
I'm just trying to help everyone.

01:01:50.499 --> 01:01:53.434
Yeah, well, what's in
all these jars then?

01:01:53.668 --> 01:01:56.363
Just nasty things, you know.

01:01:56.463 --> 01:01:58.272
Nobody needs them.

01:01:58.465 --> 01:02:00.867
I know you have my sister. Let her go!

01:02:00.967 --> 01:02:05.956
Now, now, now, the selkie child
is safe and sound.

01:02:06.056 --> 01:02:07.531
Don't you worry.

01:02:13.563 --> 01:02:17.041
I have taken good care
of the poor little thing.

01:02:17.776 --> 01:02:19.585
You're half turned to stone.

01:02:20.403 --> 01:02:22.806
Saoirse can help you.
She can help all of you.

01:02:22.906 --> 01:02:26.258
Ah, she can't help, not really help.

01:02:26.576 --> 01:02:28.302
Not the way I do.

01:02:30.122 --> 01:02:33.515
I see it, Ben, your pain.

01:02:34.584 --> 01:02:37.519
You're so full of emotions.

01:02:38.004 --> 01:02:40.064
I can see them in your face.

01:02:40.340 --> 01:02:42.900
Nasty, terrible things.

01:02:43.802 --> 01:02:46.278
They make you feel so awful.

01:02:47.931 --> 01:02:49.291
You worry so much

01:02:49.391 --> 01:02:51.742
for such a young boy, don't you?

01:02:52.686 --> 01:02:54.828
You lost your mother, didn't you?

01:02:58.525 --> 01:03:02.002
My son lost someone,
too, a long time ago.

01:03:02.320 --> 01:03:04.964
But I found a way to help him.

01:03:05.866 --> 01:03:10.386
Now, if someone said that
they could take that pain away,

01:03:11.204 --> 01:03:12.888
would you let them?

01:03:14.374 --> 01:03:15.975
I suppose.

01:03:16.668 --> 01:03:18.435
That's all I do, Ben.

01:03:18.670 --> 01:03:20.729
I take away the pain.

01:03:22.883 --> 01:03:26.944
It doesn't hurt.
It will never hurt again.

01:03:27.888 --> 01:03:29.321
(CU BARKING)

01:03:36.771 --> 01:03:39.498
No, it doesn't help at all,
it just makes things worse.

01:03:40.734 --> 01:03:44.128
Please, try to understand.
We need your help.

01:03:45.530 --> 01:03:46.515
(GRUMBLING)

01:03:46.615 --> 01:03:48.924
Don't take me for a fool!

01:03:50.827 --> 01:03:53.679
I know what's best for you!

01:03:55.123 --> 01:03:56.307
Cu!

01:03:56.958 --> 01:03:58.058
(GRUMBLING)

01:03:58.543 --> 01:04:00.728
Don't let them control you.

01:04:01.588 --> 01:04:05.858
Now see what I've become
because of those terrible feelings.

01:04:08.386 --> 01:04:10.988
I'm sick of feelings
that come bubbling up.

01:04:18.021 --> 01:04:19.005
(SIGHS)

01:04:19.105 --> 01:04:20.622
Excuse me.

01:04:21.107 --> 01:04:22.624
Where was I now?

01:04:22.734 --> 01:04:23.834
(CU BARKING)

01:04:24.110 --> 01:04:25.095
Cu!

01:04:25.195 --> 01:04:28.223
Oh. Stubborn boy, where are you going?

01:04:28.323 --> 01:04:29.423
(OWLS HOOTING)

01:04:30.408 --> 01:04:31.726
Come down out of that, come here.

01:04:31.826 --> 01:04:33.469
BEN: I'm coming, Cu.

01:04:34.204 --> 01:04:36.722
MACHA: There's nothing up there
that's any use to you.

01:04:38.124 --> 01:04:39.109
(PANTING)

01:04:39.209 --> 01:04:41.570
You'd be better off calming down

01:04:41.670 --> 01:04:44.396
and not getting too worked up, Ben.

01:04:44.589 --> 01:04:47.951
Cu! You're standing on
the door. Get off it!

01:04:48.051 --> 01:04:50.944
- Let me help you.
- (GRUNTING)

01:04:52.472 --> 01:04:53.572
(BEN SCREAMS)

01:04:54.516 --> 01:04:55.616
(GRUNTING)

01:04:59.104 --> 01:05:00.662
Good boy!

01:05:02.524 --> 01:05:04.166
- Where's Saoirse?
- (WHIMPERING)

01:05:04.484 --> 01:05:06.710
Oh, no. Saoirse.

01:05:07.195 --> 01:05:08.629
Wake up!

01:05:11.116 --> 01:05:12.758
- She did this to you?
- (WHEEZING)

01:05:13.326 --> 01:05:15.761
- (BANGING ON DOOR)
- MACHA: You see how peaceful she is, Ben?

01:05:16.329 --> 01:05:19.482
You see how I have
taken all her cares away?

01:05:19.582 --> 01:05:21.943
She is just as a child should be,

01:05:22.043 --> 01:05:24.478
without troubles, without worry.

01:05:25.171 --> 01:05:26.980
There's got to be a way out.

01:05:27.590 --> 01:05:28.690
(EXCLAIMS)

01:05:29.467 --> 01:05:32.444
Macha, please, please?
You don't understand.

01:05:33.179 --> 01:05:36.115
If she doesn't sing
her song, she'll die.

01:05:36.349 --> 01:05:39.044
So will you, and your son,
and all your kind.

01:05:39.144 --> 01:05:43.580
MACHA: Open the door!
At once. At once, I tell you!

01:05:45.775 --> 01:05:46.875
(WHOOSHING)

01:05:49.404 --> 01:05:52.214
Do excuse my little outburst.

01:05:55.076 --> 01:05:58.303
If I can free your feelings,
then maybe...

01:05:59.080 --> 01:06:00.273
- (WHINES)
- Sorry, Cu.

01:06:00.373 --> 01:06:02.484
MACHA: Silly human child.

01:06:02.584 --> 01:06:08.063
The jars are enchanted,
they cannot be broken by brute force.

01:06:09.007 --> 01:06:13.110
The shell. It caused
the jars to break before.

01:06:14.012 --> 01:06:15.737
(SILENCE)

01:06:16.056 --> 01:06:18.198
MACHA: There is no way out.

01:06:19.100 --> 01:06:20.200
(INHALES SHARPLY)

01:06:20.518 --> 01:06:23.495
Open the door, human child.

01:06:23.646 --> 01:06:26.623
Come here, Cu.
Keep the old witch quiet, will you?

01:06:27.400 --> 01:06:28.792
(MACHA EXCLAIMING)

01:06:30.403 --> 01:06:31.628
Good boy.

01:06:33.448 --> 01:06:36.592
Saoirse, I think you need to do it.

01:06:38.828 --> 01:06:40.596
- (MACHA POUNDING ON DOOR)
- (CU GROWLING)

01:06:42.916 --> 01:06:44.433
MACHA: Let me in!

01:06:53.093 --> 01:06:54.401
Saoirse?

01:06:55.095 --> 01:06:56.695
It's going to be okay.

01:06:57.055 --> 01:06:59.156
- MACHA: Let me in!
- It's okay, Saoirse.

01:07:00.934 --> 01:07:02.618
We don't have much time.

01:07:03.186 --> 01:07:05.412
I shouldn't have been so mean to you.

01:07:05.772 --> 01:07:08.332
It's not your fault, it never was.

01:07:09.442 --> 01:07:11.710
I should've been
a better brother to you.

01:07:12.487 --> 01:07:13.837
I'm sorry.

01:07:16.491 --> 01:07:18.727
MACHA: Let me in this minute!

01:07:18.827 --> 01:07:20.469
(SINGING IN IRISH GAELIC)

01:07:32.298 --> 01:07:33.899
(SAOIRSE PLAYING TUNE)

01:07:37.137 --> 01:07:38.946
- (CU BARKING)
- (POUNDING CONTINUES)

01:07:47.564 --> 01:07:49.289
That's it, Saoirse!

01:07:49.983 --> 01:07:51.051
MACHA: Let me in!

01:07:51.151 --> 01:07:52.626
BEN: You're doing it.

01:07:55.864 --> 01:07:57.089
That's it.

01:07:57.824 --> 01:07:58.924
(OWLS SCREECHING)

01:07:59.075 --> 01:08:00.175
(SCREAMS)

01:08:01.244 --> 01:08:02.761
BEN: Come on, Saoirse!

01:08:07.667 --> 01:08:09.235
Leave those jars alone.

01:08:09.335 --> 01:08:10.477
BEN: That's it, Saoirse!

01:08:12.839 --> 01:08:14.231
(LAUGHING) Stop it!

01:08:15.842 --> 01:08:17.234
Stop it!

01:08:20.263 --> 01:08:21.363
(SOBBING)

01:08:23.140 --> 01:08:24.908
BEN: It's working, Saoirse.

01:08:25.518 --> 01:08:27.743
MACHA: Stop it. Stop it!

01:08:28.229 --> 01:08:29.662
Stop it!

01:08:32.233 --> 01:08:34.126
Stop it!

01:08:35.194 --> 01:08:36.627
(MACHA WAILING)

01:08:37.529 --> 01:08:39.046
(CONTINUES PLAYING)

01:08:39.991 --> 01:08:41.466
- Stop!
- (BEN SCREAMS)

01:08:49.751 --> 01:08:50.850
(OWLS HOOTING)

01:08:52.587 --> 01:08:53.613
(SIGHS)

01:08:53.712 --> 01:08:55.948
You did it! You did it, Saoirse!

01:08:56.049 --> 01:08:57.149
(BEN LAUGHS)

01:09:04.724 --> 01:09:06.116
Saoirse!

01:09:06.392 --> 01:09:07.492
- (WHINING)
- Oh, no.

01:09:07.727 --> 01:09:10.495
Oh, no, please stay awake,
Saoirse, please.

01:09:11.731 --> 01:09:13.415
(MACHA SOBBING)

01:09:22.867 --> 01:09:26.761
I have been so lost for so long.

01:09:27.247 --> 01:09:28.689
Macha?

01:09:28.790 --> 01:09:31.015
Please, forgive me.

01:09:31.626 --> 01:09:35.062
I couldn't bear to see my son
suffering so much.

01:09:35.255 --> 01:09:37.157
I couldn't bear it.

01:09:37.256 --> 01:09:41.484
Please, Macha, my sister is sick.
Please, help us.

01:09:47.934 --> 01:09:49.951
(SPEAKING IRISH GAELIC)

01:09:50.435 --> 01:09:52.328
You poor thing.

01:09:52.897 --> 01:09:54.591
What have I done?

01:09:54.691 --> 01:09:57.584
I've wasted the precious
time you had left.

01:09:58.987 --> 01:10:02.798
You must reunite her with her coat
before it's too late.

01:10:03.116 --> 01:10:06.134
But we're still so far from home.
Do you have a car?

01:10:06.369 --> 01:10:08.553
(LAUGHING) A car!

01:10:09.289 --> 01:10:11.390
I have something better.

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:13.517
BEN: She's so gray.

01:10:13.793 --> 01:10:15.361
MACHA: Aye, you must be swift.

01:10:15.461 --> 01:10:17.729
Climb on Cu's back with your sister.

01:10:18.298 --> 01:10:21.566
You are a brave and loyal dog.

01:10:22.135 --> 01:10:25.612
May the wind travel with you,
may your journey be swift,

01:10:26.014 --> 01:10:30.909
for you carry the hope of all the Shee
with you this dawn. Go now!

01:10:37.609 --> 01:10:38.709
(CU BARKS)

01:10:39.944 --> 01:10:42.263
Go, Cu, run!

01:10:42.363 --> 01:10:43.463
(BEN LAUGHS)

01:11:03.009 --> 01:11:04.109
Whoo-hoo!

01:11:06.012 --> 01:11:07.863
Go, Cu!

01:11:12.810 --> 01:11:15.328
(GASPS) Oh, they're gone.

01:11:17.940 --> 01:11:19.040
Whoo!

01:11:36.125 --> 01:11:37.225
(CU BARKS)

01:11:47.679 --> 01:11:48.779
Whoa!

01:11:52.225 --> 01:11:54.159
No, stay awake, Saoirse.

01:11:54.519 --> 01:11:56.453
Cu, go as quick as you can.

01:12:21.754 --> 01:12:23.438
There's home.

01:12:49.031 --> 01:12:50.016
(SAOIRSE SHIVERING)

01:12:50.116 --> 01:12:51.675
It's going to be all right.

01:12:52.118 --> 01:12:55.512
We're going to find your
coat and you'll be better.

01:12:56.080 --> 01:12:57.440
Cu will stay with you.

01:12:57.540 --> 01:12:58.640
(CU WHINING)

01:13:03.296 --> 01:13:05.397
Dad, where's Saoirse's coat?

01:13:06.007 --> 01:13:07.867
Ben? What?

01:13:07.967 --> 01:13:09.327
What are you doing here?

01:13:09.427 --> 01:13:11.486
BEN: What did you do
with Saoirse's coat?

01:13:11.888 --> 01:13:13.655
Saoirse's what? Where is she?

01:13:14.265 --> 01:13:16.709
She's up at the light. She needs it.

01:13:16.809 --> 01:13:18.410
Saoirse.

01:13:23.107 --> 01:13:24.207
(GASPS)

01:13:25.985 --> 01:13:27.961
Saoirse, no.

01:13:30.990 --> 01:13:34.217
Dad! She needs her coat, Dad.

01:13:34.535 --> 01:13:36.094
Stop it, Ben.

01:13:40.458 --> 01:13:41.558
(CU BARKING)

01:13:43.419 --> 01:13:47.105
No, Dad. What did you do
with Saoirse's coat?

01:13:47.590 --> 01:13:49.524
Ben, stop this.

01:13:49.675 --> 01:13:51.411
She needs to get to a hospital.

01:13:51.511 --> 01:13:54.080
Where is her coat?

01:13:54.180 --> 01:13:55.780
It's gone, all right?

01:13:55.932 --> 01:13:57.083
I threw it into the ocean.

01:13:57.183 --> 01:13:58.700
I should've done it years ago.

01:13:58.935 --> 01:14:00.327
Now, get in the boat!

01:14:05.983 --> 01:14:07.083
(BARKING)

01:14:09.821 --> 01:14:11.254
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

